title: Concern grows for missing Cardiff woman
text:
Police in Cardiff are appealing for information to locate missing woman Tracey Jones.
Credit: South Wales Police Tracey, 35, was last seen on Wednesday 1st February by staff at the Huggard Centre, but she has not been seen since.
She is described as being 5ft 6ins and has a pale complexion, with shoulder length, black hair.
She has a name tattoo at the centre of her neck.
Tracey is frequently seen in Cardiff city centre, but also has significant links to the Newport area as well as Merthyr Tydfil.
Anybody who has seen her should call 101.
Last updated Tue 14 Feb 2017 Wales Cardiff
